SPF: Add the new asynchronous script loading and dependency management
package and the bootstrap script loader binary.  Limit both to beta builds only until the API is completely implemented.

This is the second level of support for asynchronous script loading.  It
provides a bootstrap script loader and "ready" state checks that enable the following patterns:

Bootloader with URLs

    <script>
      spf.script.load('spf.js', function() {
        spf.init();
      )};
    </script>

Bootloader with Names

    <script>
      spf.script.load('spf.js', 'spf');
      spf.script.load('other.js', 'other');
    </script>
    // in other.js or anywhere else
    spf.script.ready('spf', function() {
      spf.init();
    });

