SPF: Dispatch "spfready" event after creating the main API to enable loading SPF using an "async" script tag attribute (IE 9+ only).

This is the first level of support for asynchronous script loading.  It provides a simple signal event that enables the following patterns:

Standard

    <script src="spf.js"></script>
    <script>
      spf.init()
    </script>

Standalone Async

    <script>
      document.addEventListener('spfready', function() {
        spf.init();
      });
    </script>
    <script src="spf.js" async></script>  

Paired Async

    <script src="spf.js" async></script>
    <script src="other.js" async></script>

    // Code inside the other.js file.
    function spfready() {
      spf.init();
    }
    document.addEventListener('spfready', spfready);
    if (window.spf) {
      spfready();
    }

